This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user asked: "Read prompt.md and complete the exercise following the workflow rules." The exercise is the MHPCO Claim Office TDD kata. Per project CLAUDE.md rules, this is an autonomous TDD experiment run requiring use of `/test-list`, `/red`, `/green`, `/refactor` skills cyclically. Final marker: write `experiment-done.txt` with content `DONE` when all tests pass. Implementation must include `src/cli.ts` (reads JSON stdin, writes JSON stdout), use TypeScript and Vitest.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - TDD with Red/Green/Refactor cycles via skill invocations
   - One test active at a time (others `it.todo()`)
   - APP mass and Four Rules of Simple Design for refactoring
   - TypeScript with ES modules (`.js` extension on imports)
   - Vitest test framework (`pnpm test` runs `vitest run`)
   - JSON-based CLI input/output schema (binding field names)
   - Premium calculation with stacking modifiers
   - Component blocks (3 alike → discount)
   - Per-item vs policy-wide modifiers
   - Rounding in MHPCO's favor (ceil for premium, floor for payout)
   - Per-damage deductibles and policy cap (2× unmodified insurance sum)

3. Files and Code Sections:
   - **`/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-05-22_20-01-47_claim-office-example-mapping_v5.1-testlist-scope-fix_opus-4-7-portkey-no-thinking/prompt.md`** — Full spec read; defines all rules, examples, and JSON schema.

   - **`src/claim-office.spec.ts`** — Test file with 36 tests; 18 active passing, 18 still `it.todo()`. Imports `runScenario` from `./claim-office.js`. Tests pass full JSON scenarios and check `{results: [...]}` output.

   - **`src/claim-office.ts`** — Current implementation:
   ```typescript
   interface Scenario { customer: { yearsWithMHPCO: number }; steps: QuoteStep[]; }
   interface QuoteStep { op: "quote"; items: Item[]; }
   interface Item { type: string; material?: string; enchantment?: number; cursed?: boolean; }

   const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
   const FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE = 0.1;
   const CURSE_SURCHARGE = 0.5;
   const HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_SURCHARGE = 0.3;
   const HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_THRESHOLD = 5;
   const LOYALTY_DISCOUNT = 0.2;
   const LOYALTY_THRESHOLD_YEARS = 2;
   const MAIN_ITEM_BASE: Record<string, number> = { sword: 100, amulet: 60, staff: 80, potion: 40 };
   const COMPONENT_BASE_PER_UNIT = 25;
   const COMPONENT_BLOCK_BASE = 60;
   const COMPONENT_TYPES = new Set(["rune", "moonstone"]);

   interface PricedItem { item: Item; base: number; }

   function componentBaseForCount(count: number): number {
     if (count === 3) return COMPONENT_BLOCK_BASE;
     return count * COMPONENT_BASE_PER_UNIT;
   }

   function priceItems(items: Item[]): PricedItem[] {
     const priced: PricedItem[] = [];
     const componentBuckets: Record<string, Item[]> = {};
     for (const item of items) {
       if (COMPONENT_TYPES.has(item.type)) {
         (componentBuckets[item.type] ??= []).push(item);
       } else {
         priced.push({ item, base: MAIN_ITEM_BASE[item.type] });
       }
     }
     for (const [, bucket] of Object.entries(componentBuckets)) {
       const groupBase = componentBaseForCount(bucket.length);
       const perItem = groupBase / bucket.length;
       for (const item of bucket) priced.push({ item, base: perItem });
     }
     return priced;
   }

   function itemSurcharge(priced: PricedItem): number {
     let surcharge = 0;
     if (priced.item.cursed) surcharge += priced.base * CURSE_SURCHARGE;
     if ((priced.item.enchantment ?? 0) >= HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_THRESHOLD) {
       surcharge += priced.base * HIGH_ENCHANTMENT_SURCHARGE;
     }
     return surcharge;
   }

   function computeQuote(step: QuoteStep, customer: { yearsWithMHPCO: number }): { premium: number } {
     const priced = priceItems(step.items);
     const policyBase = priced.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.base, 0);
     const itemSurcharges = priced.reduce((sum, p) => sum + itemSurcharge(p), 0);
     let policyModifierRate = FIRST_INSURANCE_SURCHARGE;
     if (customer.yearsWithMHPCO >= LOYALTY_THRESHOLD_YEARS) policyModifierRate -= LOYALTY_DISCOUNT;
     const policyModifiers = policyBase * policyModifierRate;
     const premium = policyBase + itemSurcharges + policyModifiers + PROCESSING_FEE;
     return { premium: Math.ceil(premium) };
   }

   export function runScenario(input: Scenario): unknown {
     return { results: input.steps.map((step) => computeQuote(step, input.customer)) };
   }
